Rating: 3
This lived up to the reviews-- it was delicious, but needs a few modifications because it's excessively liquidy. Because I'd read the reviews, I actually did all of the stove top simmering with the off, or partially off. It worked out well, however, it was still too liquidy. The next time I make this, and I will, I'm going to drain the diced tomatoes. Also, I made the suggested romano substitute and I found that 1 cup was more than sufficient-- at first it tasted far too sharp and I thought it would be awful, but assembled the two parts worked beautifully together. I made my potato topping ahead while my eggplant was sitting, so I reheated them right before I added them to the casserole. I ended up using some of the oven time as further reduction time on the stove top, and it worked just fine since everything went in hot. There's one mistake I made that definitely impacted my experience with the recipe-- I added the eggplant back in too early. Bummer. All in all, we and our guests loved the taste, but referred to it as "the goo" as we scraped the last of it out of the pot into our bowls. I look forward to making this again with a few minor adjustments!

