Rating: 4
I made many, many changes and converted this to a vegetarian dish. A HUGE bonus to this is it really cuts the cooking time down - by more than half cut everything in half (except the eggplant) as I was cooking for only two, used Yves vegetarian ground "beef" in place of the lamb, used my own vegetable broth in place of the beef broth, baked the eggplant rather than fried it - also a time saver, used little baby yellow potatoes, unpeeled, used soy milk rather than regular milk, used machengo cheese rather than kasseri (couldn't find kasseri), and last but not least, baked in individual 8 oz ramikens rather than one pie dish. It was terrific, hearty comfort food that I will definitely make again. I cooked the onions while boiling the potatoes and baking the eggplant. then added the wine as directed, then the tomatoes, broth, garlic, oregano. At this point, you just open the package of vegetarian "beef" and mix it in with the other ingredients. as it's already cooked, I allowed the flavors to meld with the pan covered for about 20 minutes, then removed the cover, turned the heat up to reduce some of the liquid, stirred in the eggplant, filled the ramekins and popped them in the oven. oven time is a bit less too in the little ramekins than would be in a big pie dish. yummy